= Installing Yet Anothr aviSYnth =

This document describe how to build yasy:
Yet Another aviSYnth.

== Requirements ==
* OpenCV 1.0
* FFmpeg
+ libavcodec
* libavformat
* libswscale(?)

=== Installing OpenCV 1.0 ===
With yum, Just type a follwing command:

 # yum install opencv
 # yum install opencv-devel

From source code, type following commands after get
the archive opencv-1.0.0.tar.gz

[ Open Computer Vision Library ]
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/opencvlibrary/

$ tar zvxf opencv-1.0.0.tar.gz
$ cd opencv
$ ./configure
$ make
$ make install

In this way, you have to update and reflesh cache
of information about shared libraries.
like this:

1. Add new line and write /usr/local/lib
2. After become superuser, type this: /sbin/ldconfig

== Build Yet Another aviSYnth ==

Just do make, executable files are put in bin/